          <source>How to: Size a Windows Forms Label Control to Fit Its Contents</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The Windows Forms <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.Label&gt;</ph> control can be single-line or multi-line, and it can be either fixed in size or can automatically resize itself to accommodate its caption.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.Label.AutoSize%2A&gt;</ph> property helps you size the controls to fit larger or smaller captions, which is particularly useful if the caption will change at run time.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To make a label control resize dynamically to fit its contents</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Set its <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.Label.AutoSize%2A&gt;</ph> property to <ph id="ph2">`true`</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.Label.AutoSize%2A&gt;</ph> is set to <ph id="ph2">`false`</ph>, the words specified in the <ph id="ph3">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Forms.Label.Text%2A&gt;</ph> property will wrap to the next line if possible, but the control will not grow.</source>
        </trans-unit>
